name: BarackObama
text: b'"It is surely the pursuit of peace that is most needed in this world so full of strife." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"As members of Congress reflect on their pending decision, I urge them to set aside political considerations.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"As Americans, we should be proud of this achievement." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"Now we have before us a solution that prevents Iran from obtaining a nuclear weapon without resorting to war." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"President Kennedy warned Americans not to see conflict as inevitable. It is time to apply such wisdom.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"I have repeatedly challenged anyone opposed to this deal to put forward a better, plausible alternative." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"When we carefully examine the arguments against this deal, none of them stand up to scrutiny.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"If Iran violates this deal, we will have ample opportunity to respond." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"Worry less about being labeled weak. Worry more about getting it right.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"How can we in good conscience justify war before we have tested a diplomatic agreement that achieves our objectives?" \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'\xe2\x80\x9cThe choice we face is ultimately between diplomacy or some sort of war.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'

name: BarackObama
text: b'\xe2\x80\x9cWalk away from this agreement and you will get a better deal\xe2\x80\x94for Iran.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'

name: BarackObama
text: b'\xe2\x80\x9cThose who say we can walk away from this deal and maintain sanctions are selling a fantasy.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"We will continue to have sanctions in place on Iran\'s support for terrorism and violation of human rights."\xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'

name: BarackObama
text: b"\xe2\x80\x9cThere is no scenario where sanctions relief turns Iran into the region's dominate power.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal"

name: BarackObama
text: b'\xe2\x80\x9cAn argument against sanctions relief is effectively an argument against any diplomatic solution.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"Without this deal, the scenarios that critics warn about happening in 15 years could happen six months from now." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"The bottom line is, if Iran cheats, we can catch them\xe2\x80\x94and we will." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'

name: BarackObama
text: b'\xe2\x80\x9cThis deal is not just the best choice among alternatives\xe2\x80\x94this is the strongest non-proliferation agreement ever.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'\xe2\x80\x9cIf Iran violates the agreement over the next decade all of the sanctions can snap back in to place.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"Iran has powerful incentives to keep its commitments." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"This deal shuts off the type of covert program Iran has pursued in the past.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"In July, we reached a comprehensive plan of action that meets our objectives." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"What was once proclaimed as a historic mistake is now held up as a success." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'

name: BarackObama
text: b"\xe2\x80\x9cThe progress of Iran's nuclear program was halted for the first time in a decade.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal"

name: BarackObama
text: b'"It was diplomacy that ratcheted up the pressure on Iran." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"Winning this global buy-in was not easy. I know. I was there." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"What made our new approach more effective was our ability to draw upon new U.N. Security Council resolutions." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'

name: BarackObama
text: b'\xe2\x80\x9cIt was our very willingness to negotiate that helped America rally the world to our cause.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"I have also made clear my preference for a peaceful diplomatic resolution of the issue." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"Even before taking office, I made clear that Iran would not be allowed to acquire a nuclear weapon on my watch." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"The question then is not whether to prevent Iran from obtaining a nuclear weapon, but how." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"Now more than ever, we need clear thinking in our foreign policy." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'

name: BarackObama
text: b'\xe2\x80\x9cMore than a decade later, we still live with the consequences of the decision to invade Iraq.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'

text: b'"If we keep taking steps toward a more perfect union ... America will move forward. There\'s nothing we can\'t do." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"We cannot ignore the problems that we have, but we can\'t stop running the race." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"We are not perfect, but we have the capacity to be more perfect\xe2\x80\x94mile after mile, step after step." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"Justice and redemption go hand in hand." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"Justice is living up to the common creed that I am my brother\'s keeper and I am my sister\'s keeper." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"Justice is making sure that every young person knows that they are special and their lives matter." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"Justice is not only the absence of oppression\xe2\x80\x94it is the presence of opportunity." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"Let\'s reward prisoners with reduced sentences if they complete programs that make them less likely to repeat an offense." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"I\'ve asked my Attorney General to start a review of the overuse of solitary confinement in our federal prisons." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"We should not tolerate conditions in prison that have no place in any civilized country." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"On Thursday, I will be the first sitting president to visit a federal prison." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"We should pass a sentencing reform bill through congress this year." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"For nonviolent drug crimes, we need to lower long mandatory minimum sentences\xe2\x80\x94or get rid of them entirely." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"Don\'t just tag them as future criminals. Reach out to them as future citizens." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"We have to restore trust between our police and some of the communities where they serve." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"We gotta make sure boys and girls in those communities are loved and cherished and nurtured and invested in." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"What doesn\'t make sense is treating entire neighborhoods as danger zones." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"We recognize that every child deserves opportunity. Not just some. Not just our own." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"One study found that for every dollar we invest in Pre-K, we save at least twice that in reduced crime." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"If we make investments early in our children, we will reduce the need to incarcerate those kids." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"I believe crime is like any other epidemic\xe2\x80\x94we need to stop it before it starts." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"For the first time in 40 years, America\'s crime rate and incarceration rate went down at the same time." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"This is a cause that is bringing people in both houses of Congress together." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"Mass incarceration makes our country worse off\xe2\x80\x94and we need to do something about it." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"Our criminal justice system isn\'t as smart as it should be." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"Our nation is being robbed of men and women who could be workers and taxpayers." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"Around one million fathers are behind bars. Around one in nine African-American kids has a parent in prison." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"African Americans are more likely to be arrested. They are more likely to be sentenced to more time for the same crime." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"A growing body of research shows that people of color are more likely to be frisked, stopped, questioned, detained." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"African Americans and Latinos make up 30 percent of our population. They make up 60 percent of our inmates." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"Roughly one-third of the Justice Department\'s budget now goes toward incarceration." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"For $80 billion we could double the salary of every high school teacher in America." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"Every year, we spend $80 billion to keep those folks incarcerated." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"In far too many cases the punishment does not fit the crime." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"Over the last few decades, we\'ve locked up more and more nonviolent drug offenders for longer than ever before." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"If we\'re going to deal with this problem, and the inequities involved, we\'re going to have to speak honestly." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"Our prison population has doubled in the last two decades alone." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"In 1980, there were 500,000 people behind bars in America ... Today, there are 2.2 million." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"The United States is home to 5 percent of the world\'s population, but 25 percent of the world\'s prisoners." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"In too many cases our criminal justice system becomes a pipeline from underfunded schools to overcrowded jails." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"There is a long history of inequity in the criminal justice system in America." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"We can\'t be satisfied\xe2\x80\x94are not satisfied\xe2\x80\x94until the opportunity gap is closed for everybody in America." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #NAACP106'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"Health care is not a privilege for the few, but a right for all of us." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"We made progress, but our work is not done." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #NAACP106'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"I would not be here and so many others would not be here without the NAACP." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"Let\'s get something out of the way up front: I am not singing today." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"Happy Fourth of July, everybody. God bless you. God bless America." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"If we\'re walking down that road together, we\'re going to get there faster." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"The last seven years\xe2\x80\x94shoot, the last seven days\xe2\x80\x94should remind us there\'s nothing America cannot do." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"When the playing field is level, American workers always win." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"No middle-class family should be priced out of the education that they need." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"In America, a hard day\'s work deserves a fair day\'s pay." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"This is an issue of basic fairness: If you work longer and you work harder, you should get paid for it." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #FixOvertime'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"Over the past couple of years, 17 states, almost 30 counties and cities have taken action to raise the minimum wage." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"We\'re stronger together than we are by ourselves." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"Folks forget sometimes\xe2\x80\x94unions are what helped bring about the 40-hour work week." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"We need to boost the minimum wage. Give America a raise." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #RaiseTheWage'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"The bottom line is: Top-down economics doesn\'t work. Middle-class economics works." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"We\'ve been talking about the middle class since before it was cool." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"Middle-class economics works." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"Not only are more people getting health care, businesses are able to start giving raises to their workers." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"The uninsured rate in America is now the lowest on record." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #ACAWorks'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"We put in place the toughest Wall Street reform in history that\'s protecting main street from another crisis." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"Today our high school graduation rate is at an all-time high." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"We\'ve added nearly 900,000 new manufacturing jobs." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"And by the way, our teachers are underpaid." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"We\'ve got to make folks feel like their hard work is getting them somewhere." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #FixOvertime'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"12.8 million new jobs, and that\'s good\xe2\x80\x94but we\'ve got more work to do." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"All told, we\'ve now seen 64 straight months of private-sector job growth, which is a new record." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"This morning, we learned that our businesses created another 223,000 jobs last month." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"America has always done better economically when we\'re all in it together. When everyone gets a fair shot." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"The freedom to marry who you love\xe2\x80\x94that\'s now open to all of us. That\'s a good thing." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #LoveWins'

name: BarackObama
text: b'"It\'s been a remarkable few weeks in America." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'

text: b'\xe2\x80\x9cWe didn\xe2\x80\x99t raise the Statue of Liberty with her back to the world\xe2\x80\x94we did it with her light shining.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #ImmigrationAction'
